    <title><literal>ZapRAS()</literal></title>

    <indexterm significance="preferred">
      <primary>Dialplan Applications</primary>

      <secondary><code>ZapRAS()</code></secondary>
    </indexterm>

    <simpara>Starts the Zaptel ISDN Remote Access Server.</simpara>

    <synopsis><command>ZapRAS(<replaceable>args</replaceable>)</command></synopsis>

    <simpara>Starts an ISDN RAS Server using <command>pppd</command> on the
    current channel. The channel must be available (<emphasis>i.e.</emphasis>
    PRI Source) and a Zap channel. There is no modem emulation.</simpara>

    <simpara>The point-to-point daemon <command>pppd</command> must be
    configured to recognize a Zap interface. The
    <replaceable>args</replaceable> are a "|" delimited list of
    parameters.<footnote>
        <simpara>The list is long and complex and would not be appropriate in
        this summary. For more details, see <ulink
        url="http://www.voip-info.org/wiki/view/Asterisk+cmd+ZapRAS">http://www.voip-info.org/wiki/view/Asterisk+cmd+ZapRAS</ulink></simpara>
      </footnote>Returns -1.</simpara>

    <simpara>This application is only intended for use with ISDN lines, and
    your kernel must be patched and configured to support
    <command><code>ZapRAS()</code></command>, as well as be configured to
    support PPP.</simpara>

    <programlisting>exten =&gt; 123,1,Answer()
exten =&gt; 123,n,ZapRAS(debug|64000|noauth|netmask|255.255.255.0|10.0.0.1:10.0.0.2)</programlisting>

